  "prompt": "How would you word \"damas\" and \"chambelanes\" for an english Quinceanera invitation?",
  "response": "For an English Quincea\u00f1era invitation, you can translate \"damas\" as \"maids\" or \"female attendants,\" and \"chambelanes\" as \"chamberlains\" or \"male attendants.\" Here's how you might word it in the invitation:\n\n---\n\n**You are cordially invited to celebrate the Quincea\u00f1era of [Name]**\n\nJoin us for an evening of joy and tradition as we honor [Name] with her court of maids and chamberlains.\n\n---\n\nFeel free to customize it further to match the style and tone of the event!",
